5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to municipal employees; to amend Section
10 11-43-12, Code of Alabama 1975, to provide that a municipal
11 employee may be the recipient of a grant program, even though
12 funds flow through the municipal treasury, if certain
13 conditions are met.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
15 Section 1. Section 11-43-12, Code of Alabama 1975, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 "§11-43-12
18 (a) No alderman or officer or employee of the
19 municipality shall be have, directly or indirectly,
20 interesteda financial interest in any work, business, or
21 contract, the expense, price, or consideration of which is
22 paid from the treasury, nor shall any member of the council or
23 officer of the municipality be surety for any person having a
24 contract, work, or business with such the municipality for the
25 performance of which a surety may be required.
26 (b) Notwithstanding subsection (a), a first responder
27 employed by the municipality, if otherwise qualified, is not
28 prohibited from accepting or receiving funds from a community
Page 1

prohibited from accepting or receiving funds from a community
HB273 Engrossed
29 development block grant where the funds flow through the
30 municipal treasury, provided:
31 (1) The benefit to the first responder is similar and
32 in a like manner to other recipients of the grant program; and
33 (2) The first responder does not play any
34 decision-making role in eligibility for receiving funds from
35 the grant program.
36 (c) The exception in subsection (b) is not available to
37 any public official, as defined in Section 36-25-1, or any
38 family member of the public official, as defined in Section
39 36-25-1.
40 (b)(d) Any person individual who violates any of the
41 provisions of this section shall be guilty of a misdemeanor
42 and, on conviction thereof, shall be fined not less than
43 $50.00 fifty dollars ($50) nor more than $1,000.00one thousand
44 dollars ($1,000), and may also be sentenced to hard labor for
45 the county for not more than six months."
46 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
47 1, 2026.
